      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is SafetyWing actually health insurance?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        No. SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance. It covers emergencies and accidents but not routine care, chronic conditions, mental health, or pre-existing conditions. It's categorically different from comprehensive health insurance like BUPA Global.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why is SafetyWing so much cheaper?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        SafetyWing covers much less. They only pay for emergencies—rare events for most healthy young people. BUPA Global covers everything including routine care, chronic conditions, and mental health, which generates far more claims. You're comparing emergency-only coverage to comprehensive coverage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use SafetyWing for regular doctor visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        SafetyWing has limited outpatient coverage ($1,500 per 4-week period), but it's meant for illness treatment, not routine care. Checkups, preventive care, and general wellness visits aren't covered. You'd pay out-of-pocket for routine care.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
